        "slug": "the-art-of-silence-minimalism-in-2026",
        "title": "The Art of Silence: Why Minimalism is Evolving",
        "excerpt": "Minimalism is no longer just about less. It's about intentionality, warmth, and the luxury of space in a crowded world.",
        "content": "\n            <p>In a world that screams for attention, silence is the ultimate luxury. Start with the void. The empty space is not a lack of content, but a canvas for thought.</p>\n            <h3 id=\"shift-from-cold-to-warm\">The Shift from Cold to Warm</h3>\n            <p>Gone are the days of sterile, hospital-like white boxes. The new minimalism embraces texture, natural light, and organic materials. It's about feeling the grain of the wood, the coolness of the stone, and the warmth of the sun.</p>\n            <p>We believe that a home should be a sanctuary—a place where the mind can rest. This requires a careful curation of objects, a disciplined approach to color, and an unwavering commitment to quality.</p>\n        ",
        "coverImage": "/blog/minimalism.jpg",
        "date": "October 12, 2025",
        "category": "Philosophy",
        "author": "Dhruv",
        "readTime": "5 min read",
