        "id": "2",
        "slug": "wabi-sabi-finding-beauty-in-imperfection",
        "title": "Wabi-Sabi: Finding Beauty in Imperfection",
        "excerpt": "Embracing the cracks, the wear, and the history of objects. How Wabi-Sabi influences modern luxury interiors.",
        "content": "\n            <p>Nothing lasts, nothing is finished, and nothing is perfect. Accept this, and you find a profound sense of peace. Wabi-sabi is the Japanese aesthetic of accepting transience and imperfection.</p>\n            <h3 id=\"texture-as-narrative\">Texture as Narrative</h3>\n            <p>A chipped ceramic bowl, a weathered wooden table, a wall with the patina of time—these are not defects. They are stories. In our designs, we seek to incorporate materials that age gracefully, that tell a story of their own.</p>\n            <blockquote>\"The most beautiful things are those that have lived.\"</blockquote>\n        ",
        "coverImage": "/blog/wabi-sabi.jpg",
