        "id": "3",
        "slug": "light-as-a-material",
        "title": "Light as a Material: Sculpting Space",
        "excerpt": "Light is not just for visibility. It is a physical presence that shapes architecture and defines mood.",
        "content": "\n            <p>We often think of materials as solid—wood, concrete, glass. But light is the most malleable material of all. It changes throughout the day, altering the perception of space and form.</p>\n            <h3 id=\"shadow-play\">Shadow Play</h3>\n            <p>Without shadow, there is no depth. We design spaces that embrace the interplay of light and shadow, creating dynamic environments that evolve from sunrise to sunset.</p>\n        ",
        "coverImage": "/blog/light.jpg",
